    <briefdescription>
<para>Universal, high-level archive entry metadata. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>Unlike the fixed-size on-disk <ref refid="structmptar__header" kindref="compound">mptar_header</ref>, this structure uses spacious data types (such as 64-bit integers for IDs and sizes) and supports unbounded strings (like fully unconstrained paths and usernames). Time values like <ref refid="structmptar__metadata_1a93e2dac0ec26064fbd1c1ff7ca1d8054" kindref="member">mtime</ref> support sub-second nanosecond precision and negative epochs. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
